history.content:
Join us at our 2nd annual Town Hall event on Tuesday, February 27th, 6:30-8:00 pm in 290 HMMB!

How do you feel about the climate for women in STEM, here at Berkeley, and on a global scale? Do you believe that the Society of Women Engineers, the College of Engineering, or your local congressman can take action to improve the experiences of women in STEM? 


At SWE's Town Hall, we will be gathering together to discuss the state of women in STEM, share relevant experiences, and think about potential actions we can take with regards to the climate for women in engineering. Come to make sure that your unique voice and perspective is heard!

As always, dinner is provided. All genders are welcome!

Click here to RSVP on Facebook!
